## Multiple-comparison note

9 filters × 2 events = 18 cells. We report raw descriptive metrics only. No significance testing is performed; no correction is applicable.

## Blockers

- Per-seed variance cannot be measured without re-running the Monte Carlo ensemble with multiple top-level seeds. Current `prob_unstable.tif` collapses 100 realizations with a fixed seed chain. This is a known limitation of the existing benchmark artifacts and is listed under Axis 3 (Stochastic Repeatability) of `docs/ROBUSTNESS_PLAN.md`.
- Calibration of the Monte Carlo probability output is not in scope; bimodality at p = 0, 1 is reported as an empirical observation.
